---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import FunctionPlotter from '../../../components/diagrams/FunctionPlotter.svelte';
---

<Layout title="Linear Functions" lang="en" backHref="/explore-math/en/grade-8/" backLabel="← Grade 8">
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Linear Functions</h1>
	<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">Lines, slope and y-intercept</p>

	<section class="prose max-w-none">
		<h2>The Equation of a Line: y = mx + b</h2>
		<p><strong>m</strong> = slope (how steep is the line?) and <strong>b</strong> = y-intercept (where does it cross the y-axis?)</p>

		<h3>🧪 Experiment: Changing the Slope</h3>
		<p>Change slope m and watch how the line rotates!</p>
	</section>

	<FunctionPlotter client:visible fn={(x, m) => m * x + 1} fnLabel="y = m·x + 1" showSlider={true} sliderLabel="m" sliderMin={-3} sliderMax={3} />

	<section class="prose max-w-none mt-8">
		<h3>💡 Understanding Slope</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>m > 0: line rises (uphill left to right)</li>
			<li>m < 0: line falls (downhill)</li>
			<li>m = 0: horizontal line</li>
			<li>m = 1: for every 1 step right, go 1 step up</li>
		</ul>
		<p><strong>Rise over run:</strong> m = Δy / Δx = (y₂−y₁) / (x₂−x₁)</p>
	</section>
</Layout>
